    "client_msg_id": "23c39084-f31b-4705-b017-76b88aceadc8",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "plus, professional kitchens often work in more of an assembly line / complex system.\n\n• You may have someone who just chops meat and is abstracted away, they just deliver you the final product (internal API / SDK) or heck you get it from a 3rd party company (developer API)\n• The kitchen ops folks makes sure the infrastructure for cooking is clean, tidy, stocked, and ready to go. Line cooks may not do this (depends on the scale)\n• You can’t use a tiny sqlite database (your small pot), you need to use postgres in the cloud (a computerized, massive boiling pot)\n• etc\nOfc some of the beauty of high end / michelin star type restaurants is that they “scale up” the craft method so its made with more care, detail, but also higher cost. But this is not most pro cooking!",
    "user": "UAJKEBGP8",
    "ts": "1663248089.041489",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
